      "content": "that makes sense. so when the other side brings up the humanitarian argument—you know, the idea that human rights should transcend borders or that we have a moral duty to help those fleeing hardship—how should my students frame the rebuttal to that? i'm looking for a way to argue that the focus on universal rights might actually be detrimental to the stability and safety of the existing citizenry.",
