      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The counter-argument should pivot from abstract universal rights to the principle of *ordered* governance; while compassion is valuable, it cannot supersede the state's primary duty to protect its existing citizens. Framing it this way, you argue that an unlimited obligation to accept all entrants creates an unsustainable strain on public resources, thereby threatening the well-being of the current population. Furthermore, you can assert that a system that prioritizes uncontrolled humanitarian influx over established legal processes ultimately undermines the very rule of law that protects *everyone's* rights.",
